cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

The paper deals with computing Nash equilibrium in multi-player games, which is a central topic in game theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science - Game Theory). The paper also introduces a new function that serves as a merit function and provides error bounds, which is related to optimization and machine learning. Hence, it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Computer Science - Learning) and cs.AI (Computer Science - Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the convergence of gradient descent, which is a common optimization algorithm, and provides error bounds, which is related to numerical analysis. Therefore, it could also be categorized under cs.NE (Computer Science - Numerical Analysis) and cs.DS (Computer Science - Data Structures and Algorithms).
